## How Kernex shows up here

Kernex (`kx`, version {{kernex_version}}) provides:

- **Memory** — durable conversation and observation storage under
  `~/.kx/<project>/`. Use `kx mem search "topic"` to look things up across
  sessions, `kx mem save --type bugfix "title"` to record a finding.
- **Skills** — versioned, sandboxed prompt-and-tool bundles. Run
  `kx skills list` to see what is wired here.
- **Sandbox** — every Kernex-mediated tool call runs under OS-level
  sandboxing (Seatbelt on macOS, Landlock on Linux).

## Conventions

- Long-lived facts and decisions belong in `kx mem facts add` so Claude
  Code can recall them across conversations.
- Bug fixes, audit findings, or "things future-me should know" go through
  `kx mem save --type <bugfix|insight|decision>`.
- Per-session conversation history is automatic; you do not have to do
  anything to capture it.

## Local override

This file was generated by `kx install --agent claude-code --preset
solo-dev`. Edits are preserved on subsequent installs through the backup
tarball under `~/.kx/backups/`.
